## 6. Token Budget Management (`ai_shared.tokens`)

```python
from ai_shared.tokens import TokenBudget, BudgetStrategy, count_tokens, estimate_cost

# ── Token counting ──
n = count_tokens("Hello world", model="gpt-4o")          # → 2

# ── Cost estimation ──
cost = estimate_cost(
    input_tokens=5000,
    output_tokens=1000,
    model="gpt-4o",
)                                                          # → $0.040

# ── Token Budget — allocate across prompt sections ──
budget = TokenBudget(
    max_tokens=8192,
    model="gpt-4o",
    strategy=BudgetStrategy.PROPORTIONAL,   # GREEDY | PROPORTIONAL | PRIORITY | FIXED
    reserve_output=500,
)

# Add sections with relative weights
budget.add_section("system",  weight=1, content=system_prompt)
budget.add_section("context", weight=4, content=retrieved_chunks)
budget.add_section("history", weight=2, content=chat_history)
budget.add_section("query",   weight=1, content=user_query)

# Fit all sections within the budget
fitted = budget.fit()
# {"system": "...", "context": "... (truncated)", "history": "...", "query": "..."}
```

### Budget Strategies

| Strategy | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `GREEDY` | Fill sections first-come, remainder to overflow |
| `PROPORTIONAL` | Distribute tokens by weight ratio |
| `PRIORITY` | Higher-priority sections get their full allocation first |
| `FIXED` | Each section gets a fixed absolute token count |

