## 12. Structured Logging (`ai_shared.logging_utils`)

```python
from ai_shared.logging_utils import get_logger, LogContext, log_execution, JSONFormatter

# ── Get a structured logger ──
logger = get_logger("rag.pipeline")

logger.info("Pipeline started", extra={"query": query, "namespace": namespace})
logger.warning("High latency detected", extra={"latency_ms": 3500})
logger.error("Embedding failed", extra={"error": str(e), "model": model})

# ── Attach request context for all log lines in a scope ──
with LogContext(trace_id="abc123", user_id="alice", request_id="req-456"):
    logger.info("Processing request")
    # All log lines here automatically include trace_id, user_id, request_id

# ── Decorator: log execution time and outcome ──
@log_execution(logger=logger, level="INFO")
async def run_rag_query(query: str):
    ...

# ── JSON formatter for log handlers ──
import logging
handler = logging.StreamHandler()
handler.setFormatter(JSONFormatter(include_extras=True))
logging.getLogger().addHandler(handler)
# Output: {"timestamp": "...", "level": "INFO", "logger": "rag.pipeline",
#          "message": "...", "trace_id": "abc123", "duration_ms": 342}
```

