## 16. Feature Flags & Experiments (`ai_shared.experiments`)

Percentage-based rollouts, multi-variant A/B experiments, and analytics.

```python
from ai_shared.experiments import FeatureFlags, ExperimentManager, ExperimentAnalytics

# ── Feature Flags ──
flags = FeatureFlags()

flags.define("new_reranker",       enabled=True,  rollout_pct=10.0)
flags.define("semantic_cache_v2",  enabled=True,  rollout_pct=50.0)
flags.define("streaming_ui",       enabled=False)

# Check per-user (deterministic bucketing via MD5 hash)
if flags.is_enabled("new_reranker", user_id="alice"):
    reranker = CohereReranker()

# Toggle flags at runtime
flags.toggle("streaming_ui", enabled=True)

# ── Experiment Manager ──
manager = ExperimentManager()

exp = manager.create(
    name="Chunking Strategy Comparison",
    description="Compare semantic vs. recursive chunking on quality metrics",
    variants=[
        {"name": "control",    "config": {"chunking": "recursive",  "chunk_size": 512}},
        {"name": "treatment",  "config": {"chunking": "semantic",   "chunk_size": 0}},
    ],
)

manager.start(exp.experiment_id)

# Assign user deterministically to a variant
variant = manager.assign(exp.experiment_id, user_id="alice")
config   = variant.config
# {"chunking": "semantic", "chunk_size": 0}

# Record outcome metrics
manager.record_result(
    experiment_id=exp.experiment_id,
    user_id="alice",
    variant_id=variant.variant_id,
    metrics={"faithfulness": 0.93, "latency_ms": 320},
)

# ── Experiment Analytics ──
analytics = ExperimentAnalytics(manager=manager)
stats = analytics.compute_stats(exp.experiment_id)
# {
#   "control":   {"faithfulness_mean": 0.87, "latency_ms_mean": 280},
#   "treatment": {"faithfulness_mean": 0.93, "latency_ms_mean": 320},
#   "winner": "treatment", "p_value": 0.023, "significant": True
# }
```

---

## 17. Compliance Certifications (`ai_shared.compliance`)

Compliance automation for SOC 2, ISO 27001, GDPR, HIPAA, FedRAMP, and PCI DSS.

```python
from ai_shared.compliance import (
    ComplianceMonitor,
    ComplianceExporter,
    ComplianceFramework,
    CertificationStatus,
    DataProcessingAgreement,
)

# ── Compliance Monitor — continuous control checks ──
monitor = ComplianceMonitor(
    frameworks=[
        ComplianceFramework.SOC2,
        ComplianceFramework.GDPR,
        ComplianceFramework.ISO27001,
    ],
)

monitor.register_check(
    name="pii_redaction_active",
    framework=ComplianceFramework.GDPR,
    control_id="Art.25",
    check_fn=lambda: pii_detector.is_enabled(),
)

monitor.register_check(
    name="audit_log_retention_90d",
    framework=ComplianceFramework.SOC2,
    control_id="CC7.2",
    check_fn=lambda: audit_logger.retention_days >= 90,
)

results = await monitor.run_all_checks()
passed  = [r for r in results if r.passed]
failed  = [r for r in results if not r.passed]

# ── Compliance Exporter — generate audit packages ──
exporter = ComplianceExporter(monitor=monitor)
package = await exporter.export(
    frameworks=[ComplianceFramework.SOC2],
    period="Q4-2024",
)
await package.save("audit/soc2-q4-2024.zip")

# ── Data Processing Agreements ──
dpa = DataProcessingAgreement(
    subprocessor="OpenAI",
    purpose="LLM inference for internal knowledge base",
    data_processed=["employee_queries", "document_text"],
    region="us-east-1",
    dpa_signed=True,
)
monitor.register_dpa(dpa)
```

### Supported Frameworks

| Framework | Standard | Key Controls |
|---|---|---|
| `SOC2` | AICPA SOC 2 Type II | Availability, Confidentiality, Security |
| `ISO27001` | ISO/IEC 27001:2022 | ISMS controls A.5–A.18 |
| `GDPR` | EU GDPR | Data minimisation, erasure, DPIAs |
| `HIPAA` | US HIPAA | PHI safeguards, BAAs |
| `FEDRAMP` | US FedRAMP | NIST 800-53 controls |
| `PCI_DSS` | PCI DSS v4.0 | Cardholder data protection |

